HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2012 - AMERICAS (10): CHILE
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
1] New case, BioBio region
[2] BioBio and other regions
[3] National
[4] Metropolitan and BioBio regions

******
[1] New case, BioBio region.
Date: Wed 21 Mar 2012
Source: Bio Bio Chile [in Spanish, trans. Mod. TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2012/03/21/seremi-de-salud-del-bio-bio-confirmo-nuevo-caso-de-virus-hanta-en-la-region.shtml

The BioBio Health SEREMI [regional governmental ministerial unit] confirmed another patient infected with [a] hantavirus in the region. With this 24 year old man, the number of cases in the country now totals 28, or which 10 are registered in the area.

The man lives in Contulmo, and has activities in Chillan and Constitucion, so the health authority ordered an environmental and epidemiological investigation and monitoring of the possible places where the infection was acquired.

The Health SEREMI, Boris Oportus, added that another 4 people are under suspicion [of being infected].

Meanwhile, the samples [from the man] were sent to the Institute of Public Health and results are awaited in coming days to confirm or discard the presence of the [potentially] fatal virus.

The yound man is interned in the intenive care unit of the Guillermo Grant Benavente Hospital and with a favorable prognosis, and became the 10th case in the Bio Bio region, in which 4 fatal cases have occurred.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2] BioBio and other regions
Date: Thu 22 Mar 2012
Source: BioBio Chile [in Spanish, trans. Mod. TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2012/03/22/medicos-no-descartan-que-joven-contagiado-con-virus-hanta-se-agrave.shtml

A 24 year old young man infected with [a] hantavirus, remains in stable condition interned in the Concepcion Regional Hospital, but specialists do not discard [the possibility] that he enters a more serious phase. The BioBio Health SEREMI reiterated that the health alert will continue until June [2012].

The young man is the latest hantavirus infection case registered in the region, where the virus was probably acquired in Contulmo. The patient's respiration and heart function are monitored according to explanation of the chief of the ICU,
Leonela Ferreira, who added that it is probable that his state will become worse, to a life-threatening level.

In recent hours, the Institute of Public Health confirmed also that a 41 year old farm worker who died on 17 March [2012] suspected of [a] hantavrus [infection] had the virus when he lost his life in the Herminda Martin de Chillan Hospital. This was stated by the BioBio Health SEREMI Boris Oportus.

The 2nd case in the region, a 61 year old man, was infected in Niguen and was interned in the Davila Clinic, was taken to the Santa Maria Clinic in Santiago, where he progresses well, according to to health authorities. Meanwhile, an epidemiological team of the Nuble SEREMI carries out an investigation to establish the circumstances of the infection.

There are now 30 registered cases so far this year [2012] in the country and 12 in the region, being the area most complex, where 5 [cases] have died. Due to this, the Health SREMI reiterated that the health alert will be maintained up to 30 June [2012].

[Published by Denisse Charpentier; information from Megam Ossandon]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
